      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index benchmark validation — FDA pump geometry",
      "description": "Steady-state CFD predictions of the relative hemolysis index (RH) were compared against experimental measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump benchmark dataset across five operating points (flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 rpm). Predicted RH values fell within ±12% of experimental means at all operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The validation team noted that the solver build used for this study (ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2) is considered effectively the same build as the released production version (ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7); only a documentation patch and a minor GUI fix were applied between the release candidate and the final release, with no changes to the CFD solver kernel, turbulence model coefficients, or hemolysis power-law subroutine. Accordingly, no re-execution of the validation suite under the released build was performed.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute relative error in RH index: 7.3% across all five operating points; maximum deviation 11.8% at 2 L/min / 3500 rpm.",
      "outcomeStatus": "passed",
      "generatedAtTime": "2026-03-14T09:22:00Z",
